PRICING POLICY

Graphic Impressions offers two levels of pricing based on the size of the
file.  All prices are based on the actual file size before compressions
& modem transfer.

We offer all files under 100,000 bytes, uncompressed, for $5.95 each.  This
would include everything in normal Amiga resolution and overscan with 2 thru
Ham-8 color paint programs.  As long as the file is under 100,000 bytes
(uncompressed) it is $5.95.  To find out how large the file is use a disk
utility like Diskmaster, Shell/CLI or Dos Prompt. The list or dir command
will allow you to see the size of your files in bytes.

Files over 100,000 bytes, uncompressed, are $7.50 each. There is no surcharge
for extra large files.   This would include Toaster, DCTV, severe overscan 
sizes, super bitmaps and anything in 24 bits up to 1650 X 1100 pixels.

Additional originals from each file are $5.00 each and are exactly the same
quality.

We have a minimum charge of $40.00.  It would take 7 files at $5.95 to meet
our minimum and 6 files at $7.50.  If you don't have the minimum we will fill
out your order with additional originals up to the $40.00.

Same day slide turnaround is 100% extra and must be arranged in advance.
We can image to negative film and send you the raw film for processing at
your location for same day turn around with no additional charge.  We
advertise 48 hour turn around but the majority of orders go out in 24 hours.
BBS orders arriving will be completed 24 to 48 hours from when they are
received by Graphic Impressions.  Please do not ask for same day
turn around on slides if you are not prepared to pay the 100% surcharge.

Shipping and handling are extra. We now ship all orders US Priority $7.00,
US Express $15.00 or Federal Express $20.00.

We can bill shipping to your federal express number and we only charge you
a $5.00 handling fee.

The minimum charge applies to each film type you request.  Black & white
negatives, 35mm slides and 35 color negatives are separate processes.  Each
would require the $40.00 minimum.

Modem transfers can be paid by Master Card or Visa or by prior billing
arrangements with us.   No orders will be processed without prior arrangements
for payment. Electronic transfers must be accompanied by the electronic 
order form which you must fill out to give us the necessary information
that we would normally get with the written order form.  Please download 
the GIElectronic Order Form on your first session and include it with 
your files to be imaged. Your order may be delayed if it is not accompanied
by the order form. 

Check out our free slide/or free negative offer located in the text file
area of the Gfiles. 

New customers are required to pay in advance for the first order and can
then set up a billing account for future services.  Orders using charge 
cards with numbers that do not clear the bank will be held until payment
is arranged.  No orders will be shipped without payment arrangements
completed.  Make sure your charge card numbers are complete and usable.  We
do not take responsibility for delays in meeting your deadlines when billing
arrangements are not completed correctly. All outstanding orders must be 
paid before any additional orders are completed.  Make prompt payments to
avoid delays. 

Overseas orders please read the international readme file for payment
instructions. 

